==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flimsy
<hw>Flim"sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Flimsier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Flimsiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[Cf. W. <ets>llymsi</ets> naked,
bare, empty, sluggish, spiritless. Cf. <er>Limsy</er>.]</ety> <def>Weak;
feeble; limp; slight; vain; without strength or solidity; of loose and
unsubstantial structure; without reason or plausibility; <as>as, a
<ex>flimsy</ex> argument, excuse, objection</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Proud of a vast extent of <qex>flimsy</qex> lines.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the <qex>flimsy</qex> furniture of a country miss's brain.</q>
<rj><qau>Sheridan.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Weak; feeble; superficial; shallow;
vain.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flimsy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Flimsy
<hw>Flim"sy</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Thin or transfer
paper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bank note.</def> <mark>[Slang, Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flinch</ent>⟦br⟧
